Executive Profile
Marc L. Andreessen  Co-Founder, Founding Partner, General Partner, and Partner, Andreessen Horowitz LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 19 Board Members in 19 different organizations across 30 different industries.See Board Relationships46--
Background

		Mr. Marc L. Andreessen is a Co-Founder, General Partner, Founding Partner and Partner at Andreessen Horowitz L.P. Mr. Andreessen co-founded Andreessen Horowitz LLC in July 2009 and has been its General Partner since July 2009. He is a Founding Partner and Partner of Andreessen Horowitz LLC. He is a Co-Founder, Founding Partner, General Partner and Partner of Andreessen Horowitz II, L.P. He has been Board Observer of Pindrop Security, Inc. since February 26, 2017. Mr. ... Andreessen serves as an Advisor of ItsOn, Inc., Ceros Inc. and Asana, Inc. He is a Co-founder of AH Capital Management, LLC. He serves as a Board Observer of Arimo Inc. He served as an Advisor of Rojo Networks, Inc. He co-founded Netscape Communications Corporation in April 1994 and served as its Executive Vice President of Products from September 1994 to March 1999 and Chief Technology Officer. He served as a Strategic Advisor to the Board at Apptio, Inc. He also served as Chief Technology Officer of America Online, Inc. He served as the Chief Technology Officer at Oath Inc. (AOL Inc.) from March 1999 to September 1999. He launched the Internet revolution in 1993, with his creation of the Mosaic browser. He serves as the Chairman of Ning, Inc., which he co-founded in October 2004. He co-founded Opsware Inc. (formerly known as Loudcloud Inc.) in September 1999 and served as its Chairman from 1999 to 2007. He has been a Director of Dialpad, Inc. since November 1, 2016. He serves as a Director of Keybase, Inc., Anki, Inc., Kno, Inc., Samsara Networks Inc., TinyCo, Inc., and Octopus, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Facebook, Inc. since June 01, 2008, Oculus VR, LLC since December 2013, Skype Global S.à.r.l. since December 2009 and OpenGov, Inc. since October 15, 2015. He has been an Independent Director of Hewlett Packard Enterprise Company since November 1, 2015. He serves as a Director of AliphCom, Inc. He serves as a Director of Hewlett-Packard Enterprise Company and several private companies. He serves as a Member of Executive Advisory Board at Kollective Technology Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Albridge Solutions, Inc., Qualdrangle Capital Partners and Quadrangle Capital Partners LP. He serves as a Member of Executive Advisory Board of Kontiki, Inc. He served as an Independent Director of eBay Inc. from September 2008 to October 20, 2014 and Hewlett-Packard Company from September 17, 2009 to October 2015. He served as a Director of HP Inc. since September 17, 2009. He served as a Director of Netscape Communications Corporation since September 1994, Blue Coat Systems Inc., from October 1999 to September 2005, Orbitz, Inc. since January 12, 2004 and Zend Technologies Ltd. since September 2005. He served as a Director of Mixed Media Labs, Inc. He served as a Director of Mode Media Corporation. He served as a Director of Twelve Entrepreneuring Inc., Bump Technologies, Inc., CollabNet, Inc., RockMelt, Inc., and MobShop, Inc. Mr. Andreessen holds a BS in Computer Science from University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign in December 1993.Read Full Background




